- The years of life lost due to premature death (YLDs) is a measure of the total disease burden, expressed as the number of years lost due to ill-health, disability, or early death; 
- Mortality rate per 100,000 people is a measure of the number of deaths (i.e., mortality) per 100,000 people in the population, usually expressed as a rate per year; 
- Access logs refer to records of users' access to certain data or systems.

- 'Most recent' refers to the latest year available in the data; 
- 'Mortality rates' include the mortality rate per 100,000 people and the overall mortality rate; 
- 'Premature death' refers to years of life lost due to death before a certain age, which varies depending on the context; 
- 'Access counts' represent the number of times data for each location and cause has been accessed.
